#
# This file records checksums for passing VTTEST results to make catching newly
# introduced failures easier. A ! character can be placed in front of the
# checksum if that test is failing, or the checksum can be recorded as 0. If
# the pass/fail result for a test is unknown/unevaulated, either a ? character
# can be placed in front of the checksum, or the checksum can be left out 
# entirely. Comments are included in the output file and can include HTML.
#
